    From the manufacturer

    Ever evolving toughness: Metal-clad shock-resistant structure

    A stainless steel bezel with exceptional strength and inner case made of damage- and deformation-resistant glass fiber-reinforced resin safeguards the module. Tiny protrusions on the inner case reduce surface contact with the bezel to cushion shocks to the module. Cutting-edge technology is applied to the original G-SHOCK concept of hollow construction to deliver a shock-resistant structure with a metal exterior.

    Minimalist beauty of Form: Wafer-thin design

    We achieved shock resistance with the bare minimum case thickness by adopting a metal-clad shock-resistant structure. Optimized, high-density mounting of the circuit board structure made it possible to slim the module even further. The result is an exceptionally slim design for an analogue-digital combination model with a metal case and a comfortable fit on the wrist.

    Casual flair: Textured band

    The watch's urethane band employs a minutely detailed square dot texture. Sophisticated molding technology was used to achieve textural intricacy with incremental variations in dot size. A slide lever makes it easy to attach and remove the band.

    Meticulous detail: Dial with metallic vapor deposition

    Mirror and hairline finishes are applied to the surface of the dial to achieve texture fitting for a metal model dedicated to maintaining a meticulous level of attention to detail.

    Shock resistance structure

    Shock resistant watch for tough and rugged environment.

    200 mtr water resistant:

    So that you don’t have to worry about the watch for any activity near water

    IP colors with individual character

    The watch is offered in a choice of three colors: silver, which accentuates the hard texture of the metal (GM-2100), along with dark blue IP (GM-2100N) and dark grey IP (GM-2100B) options. These classy colors elevate the watch to true fashion item status.

    Product description

    Go sleek, sharp and bold with a G-SHOCK standard-bearer in a metal-clad octagonal take on the original iconic design.
    Forged in stainless steel with rounded hairline finish, the strong bezel says super style all the way. The dial is treated with vapor deposition finish for a meticulously detailed metallic look that suits a classic metal G-SHOCK timepiece. Incremental variations in the detailed square dot texturing on the wristband take casual urethane materials up a notch.

    • Thoithoinganba kshetrimayum
      5.0 out of 5 stars Best metal g shock in the segment
      Reviewed in India on 14 October 2023
      Verified Purchase
      The media could not be loaded.
      This is my first g shock. I wanted to buy the GA B2100 (the solar variant of GA2100 popularly known as the “CasiOak”) but when I first came across the dial of this GM2100 which is the half metal version of GA2100, I could not keep my eyes off this beauty. This is exactly what I had wanted for a long time.
      It comes with a crome finished, polished stainless steel case. The octagonal bezel is brushed on top. The dial is what captivates me. There is a lot of fine detailing on the grey coloured metal dial. The applied indices have a lined texture. The main dial has a hair like finish flanked by concentric circles. The sub dial also has different patterns of concentric circles. The sun burst effect on the dial, the reflections from the bezel, it will surely keep you engaged. It gives a slight 3D effect looking like a jelly applied on the dial when sunlight falls directly on it.
      Despite all this, the legibility is also very good. Also I have not faced any issues with the negative display. Even though it looks illegible on photo or videos, it works fine in real life. As it is polarised lcd screen, just make yourself familiar with the correct orientation of the dial when looking at the watch.

      It comes with a crome finished, polished stainless steel case. The octagonal bezel is brushed on top. The dial is what captivates me. There is a lot of fine detailing on the grey coloured metal dial. The applied indices have a lined texture. The main dial has a hair like finish flanked by concentric circles. The sub dial also has different patterns of concentric circles. The sun burst effect on the dial, the reflections from the bezel, it will surely keep you engaged. It gives a slight 3D effect looking like a jelly applied on the dial when sunlight falls directly on it.
      Despite all this, the legibility is also very good. Also I have not faced any issues with the negative display. Even though it looks illegible on photo or videos, it works fine in real life. As it is polarised lcd screen, just make yourself familiar with the correct orientation of the dial when looking at the watch.
      The resin strap also has a more premium look than the normal Casio resin bands. The square patterns on the strap gradually diminishing into dots along the length of the band makes it look good.
      Other than the above mentioned features, the watch is the same as the GA2100 with the same module.
      I really love this beast. Looking forward to add other g shocks (probably a mudmaster and a full metal square) to the collection in future. Thank you for reading my review.
